Prevention ChecklistFile 
Name: prevention-checklist.md 
Use Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA): Always enable 2FA on your university email, LinkedIn, and social media accounts to provide an extra layer of security beyond just a password.
Verify UPI "Collect" Requests: Never enter your UPI PIN to receive money; a PIN is only required to send or transfer money out of your account.
Check for "https://" and Padlocks: Before entering credentials on any website, ensure the URL starts with https:// and displays a padlock icon to indicate an encrypted connection.
Avoid Public Wi-Fi for Banking: Refrain from accessing banking apps or entering sensitive passwords while connected to free campus or public Wi-Fi; use your mobile data instead.
Scan QR Codes with Caution: Treat QR codes like links; never scan a QR code sent by a stranger claiming it will "deposit" a prize or refund into your account.
Audit App Permissions: Regularly check your smartphone settings to see which apps have access to your camera, contacts, and microphone, and revoke permissions for apps that don't need them.
Identify Phishing Markers: Be skeptical of emails or SMS (Smishing) that create a false sense of urgency, such as "Your account will be suspended in 2 hours".
Keep Software Updated: Install the latest security patches for your OS and apps to protect against known vulnerabilities that hackers exploit.
